{"ts":"2026-06-26T13:32:34.362Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-m8yl"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"CodeFactor/Maintainability: fix unsafe optional chaining (no-unsafe-optional-chaining ×25)"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"**Rule:** ESLint core `no-unsafe-optional-chaining` (CodeFactor message: \"Unsafe usage of optional chaining.\", category label \"Optional chaining with invalid undefined usage\"). **Count:** 25 (Maintainability, Minor).\n\n**CodeFactor list:** https://www.codefactor.io/repository/github/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/main?category=Maintainability&groupId=8467\n\n## What it is\n\nA `?.` short-circuits to `undefined`. Using that result in a position where `undefined` would throw or coerce incorrectly is flagged — e.g. property access / call on the result `(a?.b).c`, arithmetic `a?.b + 1`, `await (a?.b)()`, `new (a?.b)()`, spreading, or destructuring.\n\n## Confirmed instance (from CodeFactor)\n\n- `tests/unit/extensions/extension-command.spec.ts:5960` (col 15)\n- 25 total — see the CodeFactor list for the complete set.\n\n## Fix\n\nNot blindly auto-fixable — review each. Options: guard the result first, use non-optional access where the value is provably defined, or restructure so the optional-chain result is not consumed where `undefined` is invalid. Keep behavior identical; tests + 100% coverage + typecheck must stay green."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Chore"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["code-quality","codefactor","eslint","maintainability"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-26T13:32:34.362Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-26T13:32:34.362Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"claude-code-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"CodeFactor reports 0 unsafe-optional-chaining (\"Optional chaining with invalid undefined usage\") findings; full coverage suite stays green at 100%; pnpm typecheck passes."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-92if"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"afd1337aaa452d89e7a1e7d1af08b9dd1cd8a3275d6b2f8428cd8c199ca65dfa","message":""}
